From d6c174fc6f342148836c1248c3ce043560c19e29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 22:26:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 21/44] inline-3d(#625): draw all elements from the shared
 window-sized woven output
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Multi-element weave fix. The runtime weaves every submitted sub-rect into ONE
window-sized handback texture (process_atlas writes only the sub-rect, never
clearing → the output accumulates all elements at their window positions). The
async draw-back imported the woven PER-TARGET, but the output is window-sized and
never re-allocates, so only the FIRST submitting element got a fresh importable
handle — every later element got handle 0 and never drew back (only one element
wove).

Import the shared window-sized woven once, adopt the latest submit's fence, and
draw EACH inline-3d rect's region from it. All visible elements now weave.

Validated on Leia: the 5-logo displayxr-web gallery — all five woven glasses-free
3D, user-eyeballed. (Known follow-up: per-element round-robin submit cadence adds
scroll lag; tracked separately.)
---
 .../skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc        | 174 +++++++++---------
 .../skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.h         |  11 ++
 2 files changed, 98 insertions(+), 87 deletions(-)

